            <text type="letter" decls="#corresp1">
                <body>
                    

<opener><dateline><date>Posted 20th</date></dateline></opener>
<p>I have a little spare time tonight whilst the others are out
<lb/>so will begin a scrawl tho' it probably won't be worth posting
<lb/>till Tuesday. </p>
<p>1<hi rend="superscript">st</hi> business. You might send for my passbook to be ready
<lb/>for me <hi rend="underline">if</hi> I turn up, but don't ask for it till the 27<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. I shall 
<lb/>also want "my" cash. box  please. I shall probably turn
<lb/>up travelling  quite light with only my rucksack with underclothes <add>&amp; trousers</add> so
<lb/>shall be glad if you can turn out a pair of boots, shoes, <del>trouser</del> &amp; a
<lb/>bag if I'm to travel anywhere.  </p>
<p>I think those 5% bonds may be the things for you as<lb/>
 you will get good interest &amp; should have no depreciation 5 years<lb/>
hence. I wish I could say the same of the past !  </p>
<p>I have cashed a further for  <del>¬£</del> <foreign>f<hi rend="superscript">co</hi></foreign>  125. </p>
<p>I am longing to hear about the house &amp; whether you have
 <lb/>taken it. I expect now you will be simply dismayed at not having
<lb/>got a burrow in time for  b w. Shall he  postpone his leave
<lb/>if he gets it till Feb 7 ( &amp; probably a good bit further too ). </p>
<p>I cannot understand about Rex. Has he already gone to
<lb/>Havre with a draft or as conducting officer ? The family are
<lb/> very bad at forwarding letters &amp; I almost think they had better
<lb/>come via me in spite of the time. </p>
        
    

    
         
        <pb n="6558" facs="#L1916_2416_img_6558"/>
        
        
           
            <p>All my Xmas letters ill be reserved strictly till the 25<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. Very
<lb/>good of me as they give me
<lb/>quite a lot of curiosity already, as I only half remember them.</p>
<p>The date provisionally fixed for me is 1<hi rend="superscript">st</hi> Jan 17  Victoria 7.45 pm
<lb/>if I turn up it will be a deferred Xmas gift. Poor pr nothing but 
<lb/>an empty pawed BW. I hear 107<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> are not in the lines but shall
<lb/>hope to see something of them.  </p> 
<salute>Your bw</salute>
<p>Genl back from boar hunt. I think he caught
<lb/>the spirit of the chase, for his temper is <unclear>boorish</unclear> ! He ought to
<lb/>sleep well.</p>

<add><date>20 Dec</date></add>
        
    
         
        <pb n="6559" facs="#L1916_2416_img_6559"/>
        
        
           
            <p>As Mab's children
<lb/>seem likely to have a 
<lb/>dull time perhaps we
<lb/>could give them an outing
<lb/>in town as our Xmas 
<lb/>gift. Any how I leave
<lb/>this to you &amp; Mab</p>
<p>I have written a cheque
<lb/>for ¬£3-0-0. to <unclear>Jim</unclear>part 
<lb/>for the other maids at 24 </p>
        
    
         
        <pb n="6560" facs="#L1916_2416_img_6560"/>
        
        
           
            <date>Dec 20</date>
<p>Just back from a very pleasant day in the 
<lb/>trenches with 107 <unclear>Bsc</unclear>. The have done
<lb/>quite well. The men are anxious to come
<lb/>back to the Div. The Officers are not!
<lb/>Douglas was with me.</p>
<p>No more now.</p>
<salute>Your B W</salute>
<signed> WBS </signed>
<p>( 2 letters from you today but rather short.
<lb/> So glad you hit it off so well with Lady C &amp; Lady F.
<lb/>Very likely they will appear to cool off a bit later when
<lb/>less keen on the work</p>
<p>1<hi rend="superscript">st</hi>still possible unless Huns attack.</p>
        
    
         
        <pb n="6561" facs="#L1916_2416_img_6561"/>
        
        
           
            <date>Dec 20</date>
        
    
                </body>
            </text>

        
            
        
            
        
            
        
            
        
            
        

         

